Yes, the COVID-19 vaccines that have been authorized for emergency use in different parts of the world have been shown to be both safe and effective in preventing COVID-19 infections.

The vaccines have undergone rigorous testing and clinical trials involving thousands of participants to determine their safety and effectiveness. The results of these studies have shown that the vaccines are highly effective in preventing COVID-19 infections and associated complications, including hospitalization and death.

It is important to note that the safety and effectiveness of vaccines may vary between different brands and types of vaccines. Therefore, it is important to consult with your healthcare provider to determine the best vaccine for your individual needs and circumstances.